trend_summary: Early frames show several large construction pits and parking lots within a compact campus core. Over time these gaps are filled by mid-rise blocks, and a secondary cluster grows eastward toward the bridge. Some parking is replaced by buildings or landscaped plazas, while the surrounding low-rise housing and riverside greenbelt stay stable. Net effect: moderate densification.
notable_changes: Central construction pits in earliest image are fully built out by the final frame.
New multi-storey buildings added east of the main axis, expanding toward the highway interchange.
Several surface parking lots converted to buildings or green plazas.
Tree cover increases along riverside edge and within internal courtyards.
